{"id": "duc04-testb-40:2#6", "contents": "President Clinton spent Sunday visiting American troops stationed in South Korea, wearing a green aviator jacket and black cap. He addressed airmen, standing before a gunmetal gray F-16 and A-10, and discussed the threats to his hopes for peaceful engagement with North Korea. Clinton stated that \"lately, signs of danger have intensified\" and emphasized the need for vigilance, thanking the troops for their efforts. He also pointed to recent North Korean missile tests, incursions into the south, and a mysterious underground site that may be a nuclear weapons installation as signs of the potential threat."}
